<task id="remove-highlighting">
    <title><?oxy_comment_start author="steven_higgs" timestamp="20160408T115844+0300" comment="Merged into &quot;text-highlight.dita&quot; and moved to not_used"?>Remove
    Highlighting from a Document<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Managing Highlights <indexterm>Remove highlights</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Edit Menu (Review submenu <indexterm>Remove highlight(s)</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
    <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>To remove highlighting from the document you are editing, follow these steps:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Either select the text you want to remove highlighting from using your cursor, or press
          <uicontrol conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/ctrl_a"/>
          if you want to select all of the text.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the small arrow next to the <uicontrol><image
              href="../img/ContentHighlight20.png"/>Highlight</uicontrol> icon and select
            <uicontrol>No color (erase)</uicontrol>, or right-click the highlighted content and
          select <uicontrol>Remove highlight(s)</uicontrol> (or select the action from the <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Review</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> menu).</cmd>
        <stepresult>The highlighting is removed.</stepresult>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Highlight</uicontrol> icon to exit the highlighting mode.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
